## Conclusion
Custom Suricata rules successfully detected simulated exfiltration attempts via HTTP POST, DNS tunneling, and ICMP.  
Rule tuning (payload size thresholds, regex for long queries, exclusion of normal POST bodies) ensured accurate detection with minimal false positives.

### Recommendations
- Enable deep packet inspection for outbound traffic.  
- Monitor for anomalous DNS queries and ICMP payloads.  
- Integrate Suricata alerts into SIEM for correlation.  
- Deploy Data Loss Prevention (DLP) solutions for layered defense.  

